name: TrapImagePlacementTypes

properties.name: CENTER_EDGES
properties.description: Creates a trap that straddles the edge between vector objects and bitmap images.

properties.name: CHOKE
properties.description: Causes vector objects to overlap abutting images.

properties.name: IMAGE_NEUTRAL_DENSITY
properties.description: Applies the same trapping rules as used elsewhere in the document. Note: When used to trap an object to a photograph, can result in noticeably uneven edges as the trap moves from one side of the edge to another.

properties.name: IMAGES_OVER_SPREAD
properties.description: Causes bitmap images to overlap the abutting objects.

description: Options for trap placement between vector objects and bitmap images.
